Q1. What is SAP ERP? 
         SAP is an ERP software that integrates various business functions such as Finance, Procurement, Sales, Manufacturing, and Human Resources into a single system. 
         
         It enables organizations to streamline processes, improve data consistency, and support business operations through a centralized platform. 
         
         SAP Security is responsible for managing users, roles, and authorizations to ensure secure and compliant access to SAP systems.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q2. What is an Authorization?

         Authorization is a permission granted to a user that allows them to perform specific activities within SAP. SAP verifies these permissions through authorization objects and values assigned via roles.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q3. What is an Authorization Object?

         An Authorization Object is a collection of fields that SAP checks during authorization validation. It acts as a container for authorization values.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q4. "A third-party application connects to SAP through ODBC/RFC. Which user type should be used?"
          Generally a Communication User is recommended because it is intended for external application and interface communication. System Users are typically reserved for internal system-to-system technical communication and background processing.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q5. What is the purpose of SU24?
    To maintain authorization defaults and check indicators for transactions so that authorization objects are automatically proposed in PFCG.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q6. What is the difference between SU22 and SU24?
    SU22: SAP-delivered authorization defaults.
    SU24: Customer-maintained authorization defaults.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q7. What is SU25 used for?
    After upgrades, SU25 copies SAP authorization defaults from SU22 to SU24 and adjusts customer data.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q8. Why is SU24 important?
    It reduces manual role maintenance, improves role quality, and ensures correct authorization objects are proposed during role creation.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q9: What is the difference between "Check" and "Check/Maintain" in SU24?
    Both perform authorization checks during transaction execution.
    Check/Maintain proposes the authorization object in PFCG for role maintenance.
    Check performs the runtime check but does not propose the object in PFCG.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q10: What is the purpose of the Parameters tab in SU01?
    No. Parameters only provide default values on screens. They have nothing to do with transaction authorization or role assignment.
